cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DL

This paper discusses the construction of knowledge graphs, which involves handling large amounts of data and extracting semantic information. This aligns with the sub-categories of cs.DB (databases), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). Additionally, the use of RESTful web services and JSON Schema/JSON Meta Schema suggests a focus on web technologies and data representation, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.DL (machine learning and data mining).
